import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.countplot(x="zip_code", data=data, color='blue')
    chart.set_xticklabels(chart.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90)
    chart.axhline(y=data['zip_code'].value_counts().mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Mean')
    chart.legend(loc='upper right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.countplot(x="city", data=data, order=data['city'].value_counts().index)
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90, ha="right")
    ax.set_xlabel('City')
    ax.set_ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of cities in the dataset?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    state_counts = data['state'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(state_counts, labels=state_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of states in the dataset?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    ax = sns.countplot(x="county", data=data, palette="Set3")
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha="right")
    ax.axhline(y=0, color="k", clip_on=False)
    ax.set_xlabel("County")
    ax.set_ylabel("Frequency")
    plt.title("What is the distribution of counties in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
